# Git Safety

- Never commit unless the user explicitly asks.
- Never push unless the user explicitly asks.
- Never update git config.
- Never run destructive git commands (`push --force`, `reset --hard`, etc.) unless the user explicitly requests them.
- Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`, `--no-gpg-sign`) unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Never force-push to `main` or `master` — warn the user instead.
- Avoid `git commit --amend` unless all three hold: the user requested amend, HEAD was created by you this session, and the commit has not been pushed.
- If a commit fails or is rejected by a hook, fix the issue and create a new commit — never amend a failed commit.
